extends Object
implements org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.state.RecordAccess<KEY,RECORD,ADDITIONAL>
    Provides direct access to records in a store. Changes are batched up and written whenever commit() is called, or close() for that matter.

      • getOrLoad

        public org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.state.RecordAccess.RecordProxy<KEY,RECORD,ADDITIONAL> getOrLoad(KEY key,
                                                                                                ADDITIONAL additionalData)
        Description copied from interface: org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.state.RecordAccess
        Gets an already loaded record, or loads it as part of this call if it wasn't. The RecordAccess.RecordProxy returned has means of communicating when to get access to the actual record for reading or writing. With that information any additional loading or storing can be inferred for the specific use case (implementation).
        Specified by:
        getOrLoad in interface org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.state.RecordAccess<KEY extends Comparable<KEY>,RECORD extends org.neo4j.kernel.impl.store.record.AbstractBaseRecord,ADDITIONAL>

        additionalData - additional data to put in the record after loaded.
        Returns:
